Canadiens, Sabres, Sharks Win Opening Games in NHL Quarterfinal Series

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-04-15T05:36:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/canadiens-sabres-sharks-win-opening-games-in-nhl-postseason-games.html
Brian Gionta scored both goals as
the  Montreal Canadiens  won the opening game of their National
Hockey League playoff series against the Boston Bruins 2-0.  Also last night, the Buffalo Sabres began the postseason
with a 1-0 win over the  Philadelphia Flyers  behind a Patrick Kaleta goal in the third period.  The Canadiens and Bruins return to TD Garden in Boston
tomorrow to continue their best-of-seven series. The Sabres and
Flyers also meet again at Wells Fargo Center in Philadelphia for
Game 2.  In last nightâ€™s third game, Joe Pavelski had the winning
goal as the San Jose Sharks beat the Los Angeles Kings 3-2 in
overtime after the teams tied 2-2 in regulation play.  The eighth-seeded  New York Rangers  will seek to tie their
series at 1-1 tonight against the top-seeded Washington Capitals
at the Verizon Center in Washington.  Also today, the Pittsburgh Penguins, Nashville Predators
and Vancouver Canucks will try to take 2-0 series leads against
the Tampa Bay Lightning, Anaheim Ducks and Chicago Blackhawks
respectively.  To contact the reporter on this story:
